# Normality test is performed for each variable according to GT grouping, and the data of each variable is checked step by step
normality_results <- map_df(variables, function(var) {
  # A subset is used to extract data
  data_0 <- subset(df, GT == 0, select = var)[[1]]
  data_1 <- subset(df, GT == 1, select = var)[[1]]
  
  # Check whether the packet data is extracted successfully
  cat("Variable:", var, "\n")
  cat("GT = 0 group data (first few values):", head(data_0), "\n")
  cat("GT = 1 group data (first few values):", head(data_1), "\n")
  
  # Normality test
  p_value_0 <- if (length(data_0) > 3) tryCatch(shapiro.test(data_0)$p.value, error = function(e) NA) else NA
  p_value_1 <- if (length(data_1) > 3) tryCatch(shapiro.test(data_1)$p.value, error = function(e) NA) else NA
  
  # Return result
  data.frame(
    Variable = var,
    GT_0_p_value = p_value_0,
    GT_1_p_value = p_value_1
  )
})

# Define descriptive statistical functions, grouped by GT
describe_variable <- function(var, var_name) {
  # The group calculation is based on GT=0 and GT=1
  data_0 <- df %>% filter(GT == 0) %>% pull(!!sym(var_name))
  data_1 <- df %>% filter(GT == 1) %>% pull(!!sym(var_name))
  
  cat("Processing variable:", var_name, "\n")
  
  # Described using mean ± standard deviation
  if (var_name %in% c("inline_ratio", "outline_ratio")) {
    mean_sd_0 <- paste0(round(mean(data_0, na.rm = TRUE), 2), " ± ", round(sd(data_0, na.rm = TRUE), 2))
    mean_sd_1 <- paste0(round(mean(data_1, na.rm = TRUE), 2), " ± ", round(sd(data_1, na.rm = TRUE), 2))
    cat("Mean ± SD for", var_name, "in GT=0:", mean_sd_0, "\n")
    cat("Mean ± SD for", var_name, "in GT=1:", mean_sd_1, "\n")
    return(data.frame(
      Variable = var_name,
      GT = c(0, 1),
      Statistic = c(mean_sd_0, mean_sd_1)
    ))
  } else {
    # Median and quartile descriptions were used
    med_iqr_0 <- paste0(median(data_0, na.rm = TRUE), " (", quantile(data_0, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE), ", ", quantile(data_0, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE), ")")
    med_iqr_1 <- paste0(median(data_1, na.rm = TRUE), " (", quantile(data_1, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE), ", ", quantile(data_1, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE), ")")
    cat("Median (Q1, Q3) for", var_name, "in GT=0:", med_iqr_0, "\n")
    cat("Median (Q1, Q3) for", var_name, "in GT=1:", med_iqr_1, "\n")
    return(data.frame(
      Variable = var_name,
      GT = c(0, 1),
      Statistic = c(med_iqr_0, med_iqr_1)
    ))
  }
}

# Descriptive statistics were performed for each variable grouped by GT
descriptive_stats <- map_df(colnames(df)[colnames(df) != "GT"], function(var) {
  describe_variable(df[[var]], var)
})

# t-test or Wilcoxon test for every quantitative data
# Define functions to perform statistical tests
perform_stat_test <- function(var, var_name) {
  # Extract data for GT=0 and GT=1
  data_0 <- subset(df, GT == 0, select = var)[[1]]
  data_1 <- subset(df, GT == 1, select = var)[[1]]
  
  # Example Initialize the statistics result
  test_stat <- NA
  p_value <- NA
  test_type <- NA
  
  # Select t-test or Wilcoxon test according to normality
  if (var_name %in% c("inline_ratio", "outline_ratio")) {
    # t-test
    test_result <- tryCatch(t.test(data_0, data_1), error = function(e) NULL)
    if (!is.null(test_result)) {
      test_stat <- test_result$statistic
      p_value <- test_result$p.value
      test_type <- "t-test"
    }
  } else {
    # Wilcoxon test
    test_result <- tryCatch(wilcox.test(data_0, data_1), error = function(e) NULL)
    if (!is.null(test_result)) {
      test_stat <- test_result$statistic
      p_value <- test_result$p.value
      test_type <- "Wilcoxon test"
    }
  }
  
  # Return result
  data.frame(
    Variable = var_name,
    Test_Type = test_type,
    Statistic = test_stat,
    P_Value = p_value
  )
}

# Statistical tests are performed for each independent variable
statistical_test_results <- map_df(colnames(df)[colnames(df) != "GT"], function(var) {
  perform_stat_test(var, var)
})

# Output statistical test results

#Univariate logistic regression
library(dplyr)
library(broom)
library(xlsx)
data <- "E:/R/11.18_Fixed_ExtractFeatures_including PCA 2nd^echo com.xlsx"
ds <- read.xlsx(data, 1)

# Make sure GT is a factor variable
ds$GT <- as.factor(ds$GT)

# Initializes an empty data box to store the results
results <- data.frame(Variable = character(), OR = numeric(), CI_lower = numeric(), CI_upper = numeric(), 
                      p_value = numeric(), Z_value = numeric(), SE = numeric(), Statistic = numeric(),
                      stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Univariate logistic regression is performed for each independent variable
for (var in names(ds)[!names(ds) %in% "GT"]) {
  ds[[var]] <- as.numeric(ds[[var]])
  
  # Fit logistic regression model
  formula <- as.formula(paste("GT ~", var))
  model <- glm(formula, data = ds, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
  
  # Extract model results
  coefficients <- summary(model)$coefficients[2, ]
  or <- exp(coefficients["Estimate"])
  conf_int <- exp(confint(model)[2, ])
  p_value <- coefficients["Pr(>|z|)"]
  z_value <- coefficients["z value"]
  se <- coefficients["Std. Error"]
  statistic <- coefficients["Estimate"] / se
  
  # Add the result to the data box
  results <- results %>%
    add_row(Variable = var,
            OR = or,
            CI_lower = conf_int[1],
            CI_upper = conf_int[2],
            p_value = p_value,
            Z_value = z_value,
            SE = se,
            Statistic = statistic)
}

# Output result
print(results)

# Multivariate logistic model——Bidirectional stepwise regression

# After the calculation of VIF variance expansion factor, since VIF > 10 indicates obvious collinearity, the following operations are done:
# spina_ratio and solid_ratio are deleted, because they have obvious collinearity with the following echo indicators
# After deletion, the VIF of the included factors is < 10
library(dplyr)
library(broom)
library(openxlsx)
library(caret)  # It is used to calculate evaluation indexes such as confusion matrix
## 载入需要的程序包：ggplot2
## 
## 载入程序包：'ggplot2'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:psych':
## 
##     %+%, alpha
## 载入需要的程序包：lattice
## 
## 载入程序包：'caret'
## The following object is masked from 'package:purrr':
## 
##     lift
data <- "E:/R/11.18_Fixed_ExtractFeatures_including PCA 2nd^echo com.xlsx"
ds <- read.xlsx(data, 1)

# Make sure that the dependent variable is a factor type
ds$GT <- as.factor(ds$GT)

# Build an initial full model (with all independent variables)
full_model <- glm(GT ~ ., data = ds, family = binomial(link = "logit"))

# Use the step() function for bidirectional stepwise regression
# AIC is selected as the model selection criterion by default
stepwise_model <- step(
  full_model,
  direction = "both",  
  trace = TRUE         
)

#Comprehensive ROC curves for each independent variable and multifactor model
library(pROC)
library(ggplot2)
library(openxlsx)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

data <- "E:/R/01.16_Fixed_ExtractFeatures_including PCA 2nd^echo com_pre_ML&DL.xlsx"
ds <- read.xlsx(data, 2)
ds$GT <- as.factor(ds$GT)

# Create an empty data box to store curve data and performance indicators
roc_data <- data.frame(Specificity = numeric(), Sensitivity = numeric(), Variable = character())
auc_info <- data.frame(Variable = character(), AUC = numeric(), CI_lower = numeric(), CI_upper = numeric(),
                       Sensitivity = numeric(), Specificity = numeric(), Accuracy = numeric(), F1 = numeric(), Cutoff = numeric())

# Generate univariate logistic regression performance metrics and ROC curves for each independent variable
cutoff <- 0.8 
for (var in names(ds)[!names(ds) %in% "GT"]) {
  ds[[var]] <- as.numeric(ds[[var]])
  
  # Fit logistic regression model
  formula <- as.formula(paste("GT ~", var))
  model <- glm(formula, data = ds, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
  
  # Prediction probability
  pred_probs <- predict(model, type = "response")
  
  # Calculated classification result
  pred_class <- ifelse(pred_probs > cutoff, 1, 0)
  actual_class <- as.numeric(as.character(ds$GT))
  
  # Confusion matrix
  tp <- sum(pred_class == 1 & actual_class == 1)
  tn <- sum(pred_class == 0 & actual_class == 0)
  fp <- sum(pred_class == 1 & actual_class == 0)
  fn <- sum(pred_class == 0 & actual_class == 1)
  
  sensitivity <- tp / (tp + fn)  
  specificity <- tn / (tn + fp)  
  accuracy <- (tp + tn) / (tp + tn + fp + fn)  
  precision <- tp / (tp + fp)  
  f1 <- 2 * (precision * sensitivity) / (precision + sensitivity)  
  ppv <- tp / (tp + fp)  
  npv <- tn / (tn + fn)  
  
  # Calculated ROC curve
  roc_obj <- roc(ds$GT, pred_probs, quiet = TRUE)
  temp <- data.frame(Specificity = 1 - roc_obj$specificities,
                     Sensitivity = roc_obj$sensitivities,
                     Variable = var)
  roc_data <- bind_rows(roc_data, temp)
  
  # The AUC and 95%CI were calculated
  auc_val <- auc(roc_obj)
  ci <- ci.auc(roc_obj)
  
  # Example Add the data to the performance counter data box
  auc_info <- bind_rows(auc_info, data.frame(Variable = var,
                                             AUC = as.numeric(auc_val),
                                             CI_lower = as.numeric(ci[1]),
                                             CI_upper = as.numeric(ci[3]),
                                             Sensitivity = sensitivity,
                                             Specificity = specificity,
                                             Accuracy = accuracy,
                                             F1 = f1,
                                             PPV = ppv,
                                             NPV = npv,
                                             Cutoff = cutoff))
}
auc_info
ggplot() +
  geom_line(data = roc_data %>% filter(Variable != "pre_ML_DL"),
            aes(x = Specificity, y = Sensitivity, color = Variable), size = 1) +
  geom_line(data = roc_data %>% filter(Variable == "pre_ML_DL"),
            aes(x = Specificity, y = Sensitivity, color = Variable), size = 1.5) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      "aspect_ratio" = "purple",       
      "unclear" = "orange",

      "CA_PCA" = "green",             
      "solid_ratio" = "cyan",          
      "echo_com" = "blue",            
      "pre_ML_DL" = "red"              
    ),
    labels = c(
      "aspect_ratio" = "Aspect ratio_QXAI model (AUC: 0.64 [0.59, 0.68])",
      "unclear" = "Margin__QXAI model (AUC: 0.55 [0.51, 0.60])", 
      "Shape_PCA" = "Shape_QXAI model (AUC: 0.60 [0.55, 0.65])",
      "CA_PCA" = "Calcification_QXAI model (AUC: 0.59 [0.54, 0.63])",
      "solid_ratio" = "Component_QXAI model (AUC: 0.61 [0.56, 0.65])",
      "echo_com" = "Echogenicity_QXAI model (AUC: 0.54 [0.49, 0.59])",
      "pre_ML_DL" = "Comprehensive QXAI model (AUC: 0.73 [0.68, 0.77])"
    ),
    breaks = c(
      "aspect_ratio", 
      "unclear", 
      "Shape_PCA", 
      "CA_PCA", 
      "solid_ratio", 
      "echo_com", 
      "pre_ML_DL"  
    )

  labs(
    title = "ROC Curves for Individual and Comprehensive US-QXAI Feature Models",

library(xlsx)
library(pROC)  
data <- "E:/R/luoyang/11.19_luoyang_Fixed_ExtractFeatures_logistic_miss diagnosis.xlsx"
dq <- read.xlsx(data, 2)
roc_curve <- roc(dq$GT, dq$probability_regularization)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
plot(roc_curve, main="ROC Curve", col="blue", lwd=2)

## [1] "AUC value:  0.660903466395457"

# Set the seed to ensure repeatable results

set.seed(123)

n_bootstrap <- 1000
bootstrap_cutoffs <- vector("list", n_bootstrap)

for(i in 1:n_bootstrap) {
  sampled_indices <- sample(1:nrow(dq), replace = TRUE)
  bootstrap_data <- dq[sampled_indices, ]
  roc_bootstrap <- tryCatch({
    roc(bootstrap_data$GT, bootstrap_data$probability_regularization)
  }, error = function(e) NULL)
  
  if (!is.null(roc_bootstrap)) {
    suppressMessages({
      bootstrap_cutoffs[[i]] <- coords(roc_bootstrap, "best", ret="threshold")
    })
  } else {
    bootstrap_cutoffs[[i]] <- NA
  }
}

## Setting direction: controls < cases
bootstrap_cutoffs <- unlist(bootstrap_cutoffs)
bootstrap_cutoffs <- na.omit(bootstrap_cutoffs)

lower_ci <- quantile(bootstrap_cutoffs, 0.025)
upper_ci <- quantile(bootstrap_cutoffs, 0.975)

cat("Best cutoff 95% CI: [", lower_ci, ", ", upper_ci, "]", sep="")
## Best cutoff 95% CI: [0.537778, 0.7711066]
#luoyang city testset
library(pROC)
library(ggplot2)

# Load data
data <- "E:/R/luoyang/01.20_zyt_ly_MLDL_updown.xlsx"
dc <- read.xlsx(data, 3)

# Ensure that the variables in the verification set dc are consistent with the training set
dc$GT <- as.factor(dc$GT)  # Make sure GT is a factor

# Define the independent variable and dependent variable
independent_var <- dc$regularization_M_pres_p_2.0
dependent_var <- dc$GT

# Check for NA values
if (any(is.na(independent_var)) || any(is.na(dependent_var))) {
  stop("Missing values detected in the data.")
}

# Calculate AUC and ROC
roc_obj <- roc(dependent_var, independent_var, levels = levels(dependent_var))
## Setting direction: controls < cases
auc_value <- auc(roc_obj)
ci <- ci.auc(roc_obj)  # Calculate 95% confidence interval for AUC

# Calculate F1 score
threshold <- as.numeric(coords(roc_obj, "best", ret = "threshold")[[1]])
predictions <- ifelse(independent_var >= threshold, levels(dependent_var)[2], levels(dependent_var)[1])
tp <- sum(predictions == levels(dependent_var)[2] & dependent_var == levels(dependent_var)[2])
fp <- sum(predictions == levels(dependent_var)[2] & dependent_var == levels(dependent_var)[1])
fn <- sum(predictions == levels(dependent_var)[1] & dependent_var == levels(dependent_var)[2])
tn <- sum(predictions == levels(dependent_var)[1] & dependent_var == levels(dependent_var)[1])

# Calculate performance metrics
# Calculate performance metrics
precision <- tp / (tp + fp)
recall <- tp / (tp + fn)
F1 <- 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)
specificity <- tn / (tn + fp)
accuracy <- (tp + tn) / (tp + tn + fp + fn)
ppv <- tp / (tp + fp)  # Positive Predictive Value (PPV)
npv <- tn / (tn + fn)  # Negative Predictive Value (NPV)

# Display results
cat("AUC:", auc_value, "\n")
## AUC: 0.6764133
cat("95% CI:", ci[1], "-", ci[3], "\n")
## 95% CI: 0.623583 - 0.7292435
cat("F1 Score:", F1, "\n")
## F1 Score: 0.8085612
cat("Precision:", precision, "\n")
## Precision: 0.8415842
cat("Recall (Sensitivity):", recall, "\n")
## Recall (Sensitivity): 0.778032
cat("Specificity:", specificity, "\n")
## Specificity: 0.5259259
cat("Accuracy:", accuracy, "\n")
## Accuracy: 0.7185315
cat("Positive Predictive Value (PPV):", ppv, "\n")
## Positive Predictive Value (PPV): 0.8415842
cat("Negative Predictive Value (NPV):", npv, "\n")
## Negative Predictive Value (NPV): 0.422619
# Plot ROC curve
roc_data <- data.frame(
  TPR = rev(roc_obj$sensitivities),  # Reverse for correct plotting order
  FPR = rev(1 - roc_obj$specificities)
)

auc_label <- paste0("Comprehensive QXAI model (AUC: ", round(auc_value, 2), " [", round(ci[1], 2), ", ", round(ci[3], 2), "])" )

plot <- ggplot(roc_data, aes(x = FPR, y = TPR)) +
  geom_line(color = "red", size = 1.2) +
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  labs(
    title = "ROC Curves for Comprehensive QXAI model in External Validation Set",
    x = "1 - Specificity",
    y = "Sensitivity"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_rect = element_rect(fill = "white", color = NA)) +
  annotate(
    "text",
    x = 0.38,
    y = 0.2,
    label = auc_label,
    color = "black",
    size = 4,
    hjust = 0
  )
print(plot)

# Save the plot to a file
output_path <- "E:/R/luoyang/ROC_Curve_Comprehensive_QXAI_model.png"
ggsave(output_path, plot = plot, width = 8, height = 6, bg = "white")
cat("ROC curve saved to:", output_path, "\n")
## ROC curve saved to: E:/R/luoyang/ROC_Curve_Comprehensive_QXAI_model.png
